PrecisAmendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS Schedule No. 793 requiring that manufacturers of drugs in packages other than drugs in the form of toothpaste containing more than an equivalent of 120 mg of fluoride ion shall carry cautionary statements in the inner and the outer labels, effective December 1, 1994.
